================================================================================
EMPHORA — COMPLETE ONE-SHOT RECREATION PROMPT
================================================================================

Build "Emphora" — a Professional Intelligence Platform (eLifeBook™ concept).
A web application where professionals self-rate their skills, employers find
talent, and researchers analyse workforce data.

================================================================================
TECH STACK
================================================================================

Frontend:
- Vanilla JavaScript only (no frameworks)
- Bootstrap 5 (CDN)
- Material Icons Round (Google CDN)
- Fonts: DM Serif Display (headings/logo), Plus Jakarta Sans (body)
- SCSS — source files only, NEVER provide compiled CSS output

Backend:
- Node.js + sql.js (pure WASM SQLite — no native compilation, no node-gyp)
- bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken, express, cors
- Port 3001, auto-increments if busy (try up to 10 ports)
- Apache reverse proxy: emphora.melify.com → localhost:3001

================================================================================
FILE STRUCTURE
================================================================================

emphora/
├── server.js
├── emphora.db                    (auto-created by sql.js)
├── package.json
└── public/
    ├── index.html                (shell — loads emphora.html via wc-include)
    ├── emphora.html              ← ONLY <emphora>…</emphora> tag, NOTHING ELSE
    ├── admin.html
    ├── employee.html
    ├── employer.html
    ├── researcher.html
    ├── users.html
    ├── skills.html
    ├── css/
    │   └── emphora.scss
    └── js/
        ├── emphora.config.js
        ├── emphora.js
        ├── _wc.js
        └── avatar-upload.js

================================================================================
EMPHORA.HTML — STRICT RULES
================================================================================

- Contains ONLY the <emphora class="emphora">…</emphora> tag
- No <!DOCTYPE>, no <html>, no <head>, no <body>, no <script> tags
- File starts on line 1 with <emphora and ends with </emphora>
- All markup scoped inside this one custom element

================================================================================
EMPHORA.CONFIG.JS — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH
================================================================================

ALL data, labels, config, endpoints, passwords, ports, and dashboard routes
live here. Nothing is hardcoded elsewhere.

