================================================================================
EMPHORA.JS — CLASS ARCHITECTURE
================================================================================

Class: Emphora
- Must wait for <emphora> element via MutationObserver (supports wc-include)
- Methods: _bindNav(), _bindLoginForm(), _bindRegisterForm(), _bindThemeToggle(),
  _bindPasswordToggles(), _bindChips(), _bindTermsCheckbox(), _bindPasswordStrength(),
  _bindRipples(), _bindDevBar(), _subscribeToEvents()
- _onLoginSuccess(user): saves user to sessionStorage('emphora_user'),
  detects admin by email as fallback, redirects to role dashboard after 600ms
- _bindNav(): MUST call e.preventDefault() — logo has data-em-goto="login"
- Logo click: stays on page (data-em-goto="login", never navigates away)
- All wc.publish() calls must be logged via wc.log() before dispatch
- 4 events: emphora:login, emphora:register, emphora:logout, emphora:themeChange

Class: EmAdmin (inline admin panel, opened from within emphora.html)
- Modal overlay with: user list, search/filter, add/edit form drawer
- Actions: list users, add user, edit user, enable, disable, delete
- Calls /api/admin/* endpoints

wc bus:
- Self-contained pub/sub inside emphora.js
- Defers to _wc.js if present
- Methods: wc.publish(event, data), wc.subscribe(event, cb), wc.log(event, data)

No quick-login dev bar — login is done via users.html row click.

================================================================================
SERVER.JS — BACKEND
================================================================================

Database: sql.js (pure WASM, zero native compilation)
- Persists to emphora.db via db.export() on every write
- Periodic flush every 10 seconds
- Schema: users table + sessions table

Users table columns:
  id, first_name, last_name, email, password_hash,
  account_type, emphora_score, is_verified, is_active, created_at

Validation:
  - validateLogin: password min 4 chars
  - validateRegister: password min 8 chars
  - ACCOUNT_TYPES = ['employee', 'employer', 'researcher', 'admin']

Seed accounts — re-synced on EVERY restart (name + password + score + accountType):

