API Endpoints:
  POST   /api/auth/login
  POST   /api/auth/register
  POST   /api/auth/logout           (requireAuth)
  GET    /api/user/profile          (requireAuth)
  GET    /api/admin/users           (returns users + activeSessions count)
  GET    /api/admin/users/:id
  PATCH  /api/admin/users/:id       (firstName, lastName, email, accountType, isVerified, isActive)
  PATCH  /api/admin/users/:id/activate
  PATCH  /api/admin/users/:id/deactivate   (also kills all sessions for user)
  DELETE /api/admin/users/:id
  POST   /api/admin/users/:id/reset-sessions
  GET    /health

sanitiseUser() returns: { id, firstName, lastName, email, accountType, emphoraScore, isVerified, isActive, createdAt }

================================================================================
LOGIN & NAVIGATION FLOW
================================================================================

1. User opens emphora.html (login form)
2. Enters credentials and submits
3. _onLoginSuccess(user):
   - Check if email matches any admin account in devTools.accounts → override accountType to 'admin'
   - Save corrected user to sessionStorage('emphora_user')
   - Read dashboards config: admin→admin.html, employee→employee.html, etc.
   - Navigate after 600ms delay (toast visible)
4. Each dashboard on load:
   - Read sessionStorage('emphora_user')
   - If null → redirect to '/'
   - Populate name, initials, role, email
5. Logo on every page → links to SELF (never to '/' or emphora.html)
   - employee.html logo → employee.html
   - employer.html logo → employer.html
   - researcher.html logo → researcher.html
   - admin.html logo    → admin.html
   - skills.html logo   → employee.html
   - users.html logo    → admin.html
6. emphora.html logo → data-em-goto="login" with e.preventDefault() in _bindNav
7. Sign Out on any dashboard:
   - sessionStorage.removeItem('emphora_user')
   - POST /api/auth/logout
   - window.location.href = '/'

================================================================================
SHARED DASHBOARD BEHAVIOUR (all 4 dashboard pages)
================================================================================

Every dashboard has:
- Sticky topbar (height 54px): logo → self, role tag, username, avatar circle,
  theme toggle button, logout button
- Hero section: large avatar (56px circle), full name, email, verified status,
  Sign Out button
- Light/dark theme toggle (saved to localStorage 'em-theme')
- Avatar upload (from avatar-upload.js)
- No "Admin" button except on admin.html

Avatar upload (avatar-upload.js):
- initAvatar(email, heroEl, topbarEl, initials)
- Hover hero avatar → shows add_a_photo icon overlay
- Click → file input (jpg/png/webp/gif, max 5MB)
- Crop to square from centre, resize to 200×200, clip to circle, JPEG 88%
- Save to localStorage as 'emphora_avatar_{email}'
- Apply to both hero and topbar circles immediately
- Show toast: "Profile picture updated"
- Restore from localStorage on page load

