================================================================================
SKILLS.HTML — EMPLOYEE SKILLS SELF-RATING
================================================================================

Two-panel layout (280px left + 1fr right), min-height 100vh.
Topbar is sticky (position:sticky; top:0; z-index:200).
Right panel header is sticky below topbar (top:54px).
Left panel is sticky (top:54px, height calc(100vh - 54px)).
No external CSS — fully self-contained styles (NO emphora.css link).

TOPBAR contains:
- Logo → employee.html
- Breadcrumb: "My Skills"
- Search input: "Find a rated skill…" — filters right panel pills live, ✕ clear button, Escape to clear
- "Auto-saved ✓" tag (fades in/out after save, NO manual Save button)
- Theme toggle
- Back arrow → employee.html

LEFT PANEL:
- "Add Skills" heading
- Search input: filters category list
- 12 collapsible categories (chevron toggle), each showing:
  - Category icon + name + count badge (if skills rated)
  - Skill rows: name, coloured dot if rated, score badge if rated
- Click unrated skill → add with score 5, open slider, scroll to pill
- Click rated skill → scroll to its pill and open slider

12 CATEGORIES AND THEIR SKILLS:
  Operating Systems:    Windows, macOS, Linux (Ubuntu), Linux (Red Hat), Unix, Android, iOS
  Devices:              Desktops, Laptops, Tablets, Smartphones, Servers, IoT Devices
  Productivity & Office: Microsoft Office Suite, Google Workspace, LibreOffice, Adobe Creative Suite, Notion, Slack, Trello
  Programming Languages: Python, Java, C, C++, C#, Go, Rust, PHP, Ruby, JavaScript, TypeScript, Shell/Bash, PowerShell, SQL
  Web Technologies:     HTML5, CSS3, Sass/SCSS, JavaScript, TypeScript, Webpack, Node.js, REST APIs, GraphQL, JSON, AJAX
  Frameworks & Libraries: React, Angular, Vue.js, jQuery, jQuery UI, Bootstrap, Tailwind CSS, Express.js, Django, Flask, Spring Boot
  Specializations:      Web Components, Progressive Web Apps (PWA), UX/UI Design, Interaction Design, Responsive Design, Hi-Fidelity Prototyping, Mobile App Development, Cloud Architecture
  Prototyping & Design: Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD, Axure, Miro, InVision, Balsamiq, Canva
  Databases:            MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis, Oracle DB, Firebase, Microsoft SQL Server, Cassandra
  DevOps & Cloud:       AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform, Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD, Terraform, Ansible
  Networking & Security: TCP/IP, DNS, VPNs, Firewalls, Penetration Testing, Cybersecurity Tools, Wireshark, SSL/TLS, Encryption
  Testing & QA:         Selenium, Jest, Mocha, Cypress, JUnit, Postman, TestRail, Load Testing Tools

RIGHT PANEL:
- Summary strip (hidden when 0 skills): Skills count, Avg Score, Expert (8+) count, Categories count
- Skills grouped by category, each category shows:
  - Section header: CATEGORY NAME + progress bar + avg score (colour by level)
  - Pills: each skill is a pill card with:
    - Coloured chip (colour = level colour): skill name + score number
    - × delete button: always visible as grey circle, turns red on hover, removes skill
    - 3px progress bar at bottom of pill card (filled % = score × 10)
    - NO overflow:hidden on pill-wrap (this clips the × button)
  - Click pill row → opens inline slider drawer below that pill
    - One drawer open at a time (previous closes when new opens)
    - Drawer: skill name, large score number, level label (both in level colour)
    - Range slider 0-10 with gradient fill and tick marks 0-10
    - Slider updates pill colour/score/bar/category bar live
- Custom entry field: type any skill + Enter or Add button → adds with score 5
- Auto-save: debounced 800ms after last change → persistRatings() → localStorage
- Also saves on beforeunload
- Persisted to localStorage as 'emphora_skills_{email}'

LEVEL LABELS AND COLOURS:
  0  → No experience      #90A4AE (grey)
  1-2 → Beginner          #EF5350 (red)
  3-4 → Elementary        #FF7043 (orange)
  5   → Intermediate      #FFA726 (amber)
  6   → Upper-Intermediate #FFCA28 (yellow)
  7   → Advanced          #9CCC65 (light green)
  8   → Proficient        #26A69A (teal)
  9   → Expert            #1A6BCC (blue)
  10  → Master            #673AB7 (purple)

SCROLL BEHAVIOUR:
- Click rated skill in left panel → scrollToPill(skill): window.scrollTo with
  offset = element.getBoundingClientRect().top + scrollY - 54 - 16
- After adding new skill → scroll to its pill + open drawer after 180ms
- Header search → scroll to first matching pill on input

================================================================================
AVATAR-UPLOAD.JS — SHARED MODULE
================================================================================

window.initAvatar(email, heroEl, topbarEl, initials)
- Hover heroEl → .em-avatar-upload shows add_a_photo overlay (opacity 0→1)
- Click → hidden file input (.accept jpg/png/webp/gif, max 5MB)
- processImage: FileReader → Image → canvas crop+resize:
  - Crop to square from centre (min(w,h))
  - clip to circle (arc + clip)
  - drawImage to 200×200
  - toDataURL('image/jpeg', 0.88)
- applyImage(heroEl, topbarEl, dataUrl):
  - backgroundImage, backgroundSize:cover, backgroundPosition:center, color:transparent
- saveAvatar: localStorage.setItem('emphora_avatar_{email}', dataUrl)
  - On storage full: clear other avatar keys first, retry
- loadAvatar: localStorage.getItem('emphora_avatar_{email}')
- Toast: fixed bottom-center, border-left colour by type, fade in/out 3s
- CSS on heroEl: position:relative; cursor:pointer; overflow:hidden; border-radius:50%
- Overlay span: position:absolute; inset:0; opacity:0; transition; shows on hover

================================================================================
EMPHORA.SCSS — STYLES
================================================================================

- All styles scoped to .emphora selector
- CSS variables for light/dark themes via [data-emphora-theme]
- Light theme on :root or [data-emphora-theme="light"]
- Dark theme on [data-emphora-theme="dark"]
- Key colour variables: --em-primary, --em-secondary, --em-accent,
  --em-bg-surface, --em-text-primary, --em-text-muted, --em-border,
  --em-success, --em-error, --em-warning
- Account tag colours:
  em-tag--employee (blue), em-tag--employer (teal),
  em-tag--researcher (pink), em-tag--admin (purple)
- Dev bar styles (kept even though bar is removed — for future use)
- Admin panel styles (EmAdmin modal)
- Dashboard view styles (em-dash-*)
- Avatar upload overlay styles (em-avatar-upload, em-avatar-overlay)
- Never provide compiled CSS — SCSS source files only

================================================================================
GENERAL RULES
================================================================================

1. SCSS only — never provide .css compiled output
2. emphora.html contains ONLY <emphora>…</emphora>, nothing else
3. emphora.config.js is single source of truth for ALL data
4. All code prefixed with mtk- where applicable (class names, IDs use em- prefix)
5. Always show updated code in FULL, never in snippets
6. All dashboard logos link to their own page (never to '/' or emphora.html)
7. _bindNav() must call e.preventDefault() before switching views
8. Auto-save on skills page — NO manual Save button
9. No quick-login dev bar — login via users.html row click
10. Seed re-syncs names, passwords, scores, and accountType on every restart
11. Admin is detected by both accountType AND email fallback in _onLoginSuccess
12. users.html is fully self-contained (no emphora.css link)
13. skills.html is fully self-contained (no emphora.css link)
14. × delete on skills pills: always visible, NO overflow:hidden on .em-pill-wrap

================================================================================
DEPLOYMENT
================================================================================

Server: Apache reverse proxy at emphora.melify.com → localhost:3001
Apache config (already in place):
  ProxyPreserveHost On
  ProxyPass / http://localhost:3001/
  ProxyPassReverse / http://localhost:3001/

Start server:
  cd /Melify/tools/emphora && node server.js

Files go to:
  /Melify/tools/emphora/server.js
  /Melify/tools/emphora/public/*.html
  /Melify/tools/emphora/public/css/emphora.scss
  /Melify/tools/emphora/public/js/*.js

